<paragraph blockId="109.[189,1399,496,628]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johansson &amp; Cederberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,410,496,522]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegatus">
<emphasis box="[189,410,496,522]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Ophion variegatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in a variety of different habitats ranging from semi-open forests to gardens and hedgerows. Host records from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hubner, 1808) (Brock 1982)" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1808" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[622,1204,531,557]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mythimna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impura">
<emphasis box="[622,837,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Mythimna impura</emphasis>
(Hübner, 1808) (
<bibRefCitation author="Brock" box="[1051,1196,531,557]" firstAuthor="Brock" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" pagination="57 - 97" refId="ref63572" refString="Brock J. P. 1982. A systematic study of the genus Ophion in Britain (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 125: 57 - 97." type="journal article" year="1982">Brock 1982</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
probably refers to this species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johansson &amp; Cederberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[375,596,566,592]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegatus">
<emphasis box="[375,596,566,592]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Ophion variegatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is active from May to June in Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1087,1180,566,592]" name="Sweden" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Sweden</collectingCountry>
and flies until the beginning of August in the Northern parts of Central 
<collectingCountry box="[812,909,601,627]" name="Sweden" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Sweden</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
